WEBVTT

00:02.750 --> 00:04.500
♪ GO! ♪

00:04.583 --> 00:06.583
Charlie: <i>LIFE IS ALL ABOUT</i>
<i>THE CHOICES YOU MAKE.</i>

00:06.667 --> 00:08.208
[ COUGHS ]

00:08.291 --> 00:11.125
<i>WHAT'S FOR BREAKFAST --</i>
<i>EGGS OR PANCAKES?</i>

00:11.208 --> 00:14.417
<i>SHOULD YOU TAKE THE ELEVATOR</i>
<i>OR THE STAIRS?</i>

00:14.500 --> 00:17.458
<i>FOR ME, THERE'S ONLY ONE</i>
<i>CHOICE RIGHT NOW.</i>

00:17.542 --> 00:20.583
<i>BLINK ONCE FOR YES,</i>
<i>TWICE FOR NO.</i>

00:20.667 --> 00:22.542
<i>BUT FOR EVERYONE ELSE,</i>

00:22.625 --> 00:26.333
<i>THINGS HAVE A WAY OF GETTING</i>
<i>VERY COMPLICATED VERY QUICKLY.</i>

00:26.417 --> 00:28.959
<i>ALL OF THOSE TINY,</i>
<i>INSIGNIFICANT CHOICES YOU MADE</i>

00:29.041 --> 00:33.333
<i>ADD UP TO...</i>
<i>HOW DID I GET</i> HERE?

00:33.417 --> 00:36.291
<i>OR HERE.</i>

00:36.375 --> 00:39.000
<i>OR HERE.</i>

00:39.083 --> 00:41.917
<i>AND ESPECIALLY HERE.</i>

00:42.041 --> 00:43.458
<i>SO HOW DID THEY?</i>

00:43.542 --> 00:45.291
<i>FUNNY YOU SHOULD ASK.</i>

00:45.375 --> 00:48.875
<i>IT ALL STARTED</i>
<i>24 SHORT HOURS AGO.</i>

00:48.959 --> 00:51.208
AND THIS IS FROM MY COUSIN
IN EL SEGUNDO.

00:51.291 --> 00:52.875
AH! MANUEL RUIZ.

00:52.959 --> 00:55.250
HE SAID I CAN LIVE WITH HIM
AFTER I LEAVE THE HOSPITAL.

00:55.333 --> 00:57.208
HIS WIFE'S FAMILY
OWNS A CAR DEALERSHIP,

00:57.291 --> 00:59.375
SO I CAN HELP AROUND THE OFFICE
AFTER SCHOOL.

00:59.458 --> 01:01.000
IT'S NOT A LOT OF MONEY,

01:01.083 --> 01:03.041
BUT I LISTED IT ON THE INCOME
AND EXPENSE DECLARATION.

01:03.125 --> 01:05.709
I ALSO HAVE PROOF OF ENROLLMENT
AT A NEARBY HIGH SCHOOL.

01:05.792 --> 01:07.291
NICE TOUCH.

01:07.375 --> 01:09.542
JUDGES LIKE TO SEE
THAT EMANCIPATED MINORS

01:09.625 --> 01:11.542
STILL TAKE THEIR
EDUCATION SERIOUSLY.

01:11.625 --> 01:13.542
AND NOW THAT WE'VE GOT
THE COMPLETED APPLICATION,

01:13.625 --> 01:15.709
YOUR MOTHER'S CONSENT,
ALL WE NEED IS THE FILING FEE.

01:15.792 --> 01:17.792
THERE'S A FILING FEE?

01:17.875 --> 01:20.458
YEAH. THEY BURY IT
IN THE FINE PRINT.

01:20.542 --> 01:22.875
THERE IT IS -- $395.

01:22.959 --> 01:25.917
YOU CAN FILE A PETITION
WITH THE JUDGE TO WAIVE IT,

01:26.000 --> 01:28.000
BUT IF YOU DO, THEY USUALLY
TAKE IT AS A SIGN

01:28.083 --> 01:29.750
THAT YOU'RE NOT READY
FOR ADULTHOOD.

01:29.834 --> 01:32.458
WHAT, BECAUSE I DON'T HAVE
$400 LYING AROUND?

01:32.542 --> 01:34.208
I KNOW, RIGHT?

01:34.291 --> 01:36.000
GOOD THING <i>I'M</i> NOT TRYING
TO GET EMANCIPATED.

01:36.083 --> 01:37.417
I'D BE TOTALLY SCREWED.

01:39.875 --> 01:41.709
ALL RIGHT, PEOPLE, LISTEN UP.

01:41.792 --> 01:43.667
GOT A NEW GAME PLAN FOR TODAY.

01:43.750 --> 01:45.875
EMMA, DR. SAMUELS MOVED
YOUR APPOINTMENT UP TO 10:00.

01:45.959 --> 01:48.166
LEO, YOU'RE LEAVING STRAIGHT
FROM HERE AND GOING TO P.T.

01:48.250 --> 01:50.125
EVERYBODY ELSE IS GONNA STAY
IN THIS CLASSROOM

01:50.208 --> 01:51.250
AND TRY TO LEARN SOMETHING.

01:51.333 --> 01:52.917
MOST IMPORTANTLY,

01:53.000 --> 01:54.083
I WANT EVERYONE TO STEER CLEAR
OF CHARLIE'S ROOM.

01:54.166 --> 01:55.542
DOCTOR TODAY IS GONNA BE
IN THERE

01:55.625 --> 01:56.792
DOING SOME VERY IMPORTANT WORK.

01:56.875 --> 01:58.417
UM, EXCUSE ME.

01:58.500 --> 01:59.667
WHERE AM I SUPPOSED TO GO
FOR MY QUIET REPOSE?

01:59.750 --> 02:01.208
THAT'S MY ROOM, TOO.

02:01.291 --> 02:02.625
I'M SURE YOU'LL THINK
OF SOMETHING -- OOH!

02:02.709 --> 02:04.500
WHICH REMINDS ME.

02:04.583 --> 02:06.041
YOU'LL BE WEARING THIS TODAY.

02:06.125 --> 02:07.542
SO...

02:07.625 --> 02:09.709
KEY WORD FOR TODAY
IS "QUIET."

02:09.792 --> 02:12.125
GET THAT, PEOPLE?
"QUIET."

02:12.208 --> 02:14.500
GET YOUR HANDS
OFF MY VODKA!

02:14.583 --> 02:17.625
OH, MY GOD,
IS THAT DELANEY SHAW?
LET GO OF ME!

02:17.709 --> 02:19.291
THIS IS AMERICA, ISN'T IT?

02:19.375 --> 02:22.792
I STILL HAVE MY RIGHTS,
DON'T I?!

02:22.875 --> 02:26.166
HELLO! SOMEBODY READ ME
THE EIGHTH AMENDMENT!

02:26.250 --> 02:27.959
MY GOD, IT <i>IS</i> HER.
READ ME MY RIGHTS!

02:28.041 --> 02:30.125
YOU KNOW SHE JUST CAME OUT
WITH HER OWN CLOTHING LINE?

02:30.208 --> 02:31.834
SHE NEEDS ONE.
HER MUSIC SUCKS.

02:31.917 --> 02:33.917
OH, SHE'S NOT <i>THAT</i> TERRIBLE.
SHE'S JUST, UH...

02:34.000 --> 02:35.625
OVER?
SHE NEEDS TO BE OVER <i>ME.</i>

02:35.709 --> 02:37.709
ON WHAT PLANET DO YOU HAVE
A SHOT AT DELANEY SHAW?

02:37.792 --> 02:39.166
PLANET HOSPITAL,

02:39.250 --> 02:40.834
WHERE THE COMPETITION
IS DRASTICALLY REDUCED.

02:40.917 --> 02:43.458
PLUS, THAT GIRL IS A HOT MESS.
SHE'LL SLEEP WITH ANYBODY.

02:43.542 --> 02:44.959
YOU GOT TO LOVE THAT
IN A WOMAN.

02:45.041 --> 02:46.333
IS THAT DELANEY SHAW?

02:46.417 --> 02:48.000
YO, CHILL, MAN.
I JUST CALLED SHOTGUN.

02:48.083 --> 02:49.542
SHE'S A PERSON, NOT A CAR.

02:49.625 --> 02:50.834
Jackson: ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

02:50.917 --> 02:52.417
ARE WE DONE?
YOU TWO, THERAPY.

02:52.500 --> 02:54.333
EVERYBODY ELSE,
EDUCATION AND QUIET.

02:54.417 --> 02:56.500
NO.

03:00.166 --> 03:03.041
YO, MAN, <i>CAPISCE?</i>
WE GOT AN UNDERSTANDING?

03:05.583 --> 03:06.834
YEAH, SHE'S ALL YOURS.

03:08.000 --> 03:09.000
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

03:15.750 --> 03:18.083
UH, HI.
IS YOUR NAME DEBBIE?

03:18.166 --> 03:20.542
OH, MY GOD.
AREN'T YOU --

03:20.625 --> 03:22.542
NEVER MIND.
I THINK DEBBIE'S ASIAN.

03:22.625 --> 03:24.333
UM, DO YOU HAVE
ANY CIGARETTES?

03:24.417 --> 03:26.000
UH, I DO NOT,

03:26.083 --> 03:28.375
AND I'M SURE YOU UNDERSTAND
THAT THERE IS NO SMOKING --

03:28.458 --> 03:29.625
OH, MY GOD.

03:29.709 --> 03:31.709
WHAT IS THIS?

03:31.792 --> 03:33.250
[ GASPS ]

03:33.333 --> 03:35.250
THIS IS THE SADDEST DRESS
I'VE EVER SEEN.

03:35.333 --> 03:37.750
IT LOOKS LIKE
A GIANT DOILY.

03:37.834 --> 03:39.166
KENJI?

03:39.250 --> 03:41.041
<i>THERE</i> YOU ARE.

03:41.125 --> 03:42.792
WHAT HAPPENED TO WAITING FOR ME
IN YOUR ROOM?

03:42.875 --> 03:45.917
DID I <i>SAY</i>
I WAS GONNA DO THAT?

03:46.000 --> 03:48.542
HMM.
DOESN'T SOUND LIKE ME.

03:48.625 --> 03:50.625
OH.

03:50.709 --> 03:52.667
UNLESS I'M GETTING
THE CUTE DOCTOR.

03:52.750 --> 03:55.250
[ GASPS ]
IN THAT CASE, LEAD THE WAY.

03:55.333 --> 03:57.667
YOU'RE GETTING <i>ME</i>
AND A BLOOD DRAW,

03:57.750 --> 04:00.583
AND IF YOU'RE GOOD,
POSSIBLY A CHEST X-RAY.

04:00.667 --> 04:01.917
IT'S THE LACE.

04:02.000 --> 04:03.625
LACE MAKES PEOPLE THINK
OF DOILIES.

04:03.709 --> 04:05.417
DON'T LISTEN
TO QUEEN CRAZY.

04:05.500 --> 04:09.792
THAT DRESS IS GONNA KILL
ON YOUR DATE TONIGHT.

04:09.875 --> 04:11.250
YOU GOT A DATE TONIGHT?

04:11.333 --> 04:14.417
YEP! FIRST ONE
SINCE THE BIG BREAKUP.

04:14.500 --> 04:16.917
89% COMPATIBILITY,
THOUGH, SO [CHUCKLES]

04:17.000 --> 04:19.083
I MEAN, I'M NOT REALLY
AN ONLINE KIND OF GAL,

04:19.166 --> 04:21.959
BUT GOT TO GET OUT THERE,
AS THEY SAY.

04:22.041 --> 04:25.000
HOW ELSE ARE YOU GONNA MEET
THAT SPECIAL SOMEONE?

04:25.083 --> 04:27.583
YEAH. I'M SURE YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE A GREAT TIME.

04:27.667 --> 04:29.834
DR. GRACE!

04:29.917 --> 04:31.709
OH, DR. McANDREW.

04:31.792 --> 04:33.458
NICE TIE.

04:33.542 --> 04:35.583
WHY, THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

04:35.667 --> 04:36.917
IS THAT DELANEY SHAW?

04:37.000 --> 04:38.792
TO WHAT DO WE, UH,
OWE THAT PLEASURE?

04:38.875 --> 04:42.041
OHH! SHE'S EXHAUSTED.
POOR GIRL IS JUST EXHAUSTED.

04:42.125 --> 04:44.834
DO YOU KNOW HOW HARD IT IS
TO BE A TEEN POP STAR?

04:44.917 --> 04:46.166
YES -- NO, I DON'T.

04:46.250 --> 04:48.250
[ Laughing ] NEITHER DO I,
THANK GOD.

04:48.333 --> 04:51.208
HEY, HOW IS OUR HEMP-WEARING
FRIEND, DR. NADAY?

04:51.291 --> 04:53.375
OH, HE'S GOOD.
HE ACTUALLY, UH,

04:53.458 --> 04:54.875
SET UP CHARLIE'S
COMPUTER INTERFACE,

04:54.959 --> 04:56.333
SO BY THE END OF THE DAY,

04:56.417 --> 04:57.834
THE KID SHOULD BE
TALKING UP A STORM.

04:57.917 --> 04:59.333
HOPEFULLY THE DEVICE IS JUST
A TEMPORARY STOPGAP

04:59.417 --> 05:01.125
[SNAPS FINGERS] TILL
HE'S TALKING ON HIS OWN.

05:01.208 --> 05:02.834
THAT'S GREAT NEWS.

05:02.917 --> 05:05.291
I KNOW IT WAS A BIT
OF A ROCKY START,

05:05.375 --> 05:07.125
BUT MUTUAL RESPECT, RIGHT?
TEAMWORK.

05:07.208 --> 05:08.750
YEAH, ABSOLUTELY.

05:08.834 --> 05:10.208
I RESPECT HIM.
HE RESPECTS ME.

05:10.291 --> 05:12.667
NO, ACTUALLY,
I MEANT WITH <i>US,</i>

05:12.750 --> 05:15.250
YOU AND ME.

05:15.333 --> 05:17.625
NO. WHAT DO --
WHAT DO YOU MEAN WITH US?

05:17.709 --> 05:18.917
LOOK AT US.

05:19.000 --> 05:19.959
WE'RE SORT OF
THE TEXTBOOK EXAMPLE

05:20.041 --> 05:21.166
OF WHY YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED

05:21.250 --> 05:22.208
TO GET INVOLVED
WITH A COLLEAGUE.

05:22.291 --> 05:23.625
BECAUSE WHEN IT ENDS,

05:23.709 --> 05:25.083
YOU STILL HAVE TO SEE THEM
EVERY DAY,

05:25.166 --> 05:26.542
AND IT'S ALL RIGHT THERE
ON THE SURFACE --

05:26.625 --> 05:29.792
ALL THE HISTORY,
ALL THE BAD FEELINGS.

05:29.875 --> 05:32.792
I DO RECALL
SOME <i>GOOD</i> FEELINGS.

05:32.875 --> 05:35.000
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU'RE RIGHT,
YOU'RE RIGHT.

05:35.083 --> 05:36.166
AW.

05:36.250 --> 05:37.875
I MISS YOU, ADAM.

05:37.959 --> 05:39.333
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:39.417 --> 05:41.750
I'M GLAD THIS IS ALL
GOING SO WELL.

05:51.667 --> 05:52.917
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

05:53.000 --> 05:54.000
WAIT, WAIT.
I HAVE TO TAKE THIS OFF.

05:54.083 --> 05:55.417
YEAH, ME TOO.

05:55.500 --> 05:56.834
WHAT? NO.
I MEANT MY HEART MONITOR.

05:56.917 --> 05:58.458
WHEN MY HEART RATE GOES UP,

05:58.542 --> 06:00.375
IT SENDS SOME KIND OF BAT SIGNAL
TO NURSE JACKSON.

06:00.458 --> 06:01.625
MM, HEART MONITOR.

06:01.709 --> 06:03.291
[ Moaning ] OH, YEAH.
SAY IT AGAIN.

06:03.375 --> 06:04.667
MM, HEART MONITOR.

06:04.750 --> 06:05.750
PULMONARY EMBOLISM.

06:05.834 --> 06:06.834
[ MOANS ]

06:06.917 --> 06:09.500
AORTIC ANEURYSM.
[ MOANS ]

06:09.583 --> 06:12.083
Jackson:
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

06:12.166 --> 06:14.834
[ GASPS ] OH, MY GOD!

06:14.917 --> 06:17.792
HELLO! CAN'T A PERSON GET
A LITTLE PRIVACY AROUND HERE?

06:17.875 --> 06:19.792
NOT WHEN SHE TAKES OFF
HER HEART MONITOR.

06:19.875 --> 06:22.041
WHAT? YOU MEAN IT GOES OFF EVEN
WHEN I'M <i>NOT</i> CONNECTED TO IT?

06:22.125 --> 06:24.208
LIKE A SMOKE ALARM
THAT NEEDS NEW BATTERIES.

06:24.291 --> 06:27.417
HUNTER, I NEED TO SPEAK WITH
KARA FOR A MOMENT IN PRIVATE.

06:29.458 --> 06:30.709
TAKE YOUR SHIRT, HON.

06:30.792 --> 06:34.917
[ SIGHS ] RIGHT.
[ CHUCKLES ] SORRY.

06:38.500 --> 06:40.250
[ GROANS ]

06:40.333 --> 06:42.959
KARA...

06:43.041 --> 06:46.542
IS THAT <i>REALLY</i> HOW YOU WANT
TO CONDUCT YOURSELF?

06:46.625 --> 06:49.291
OH, MY GOD. WHAT ARE YOU, PART
OF SOME WEIRD RELIGIOUS ORDER?

06:49.375 --> 06:51.625
YES, THIS IS EXACTLY HOW
I WANT TO CONDUCT MYSELF.

06:51.709 --> 06:53.458
EVEN IF IT ENDS
WITH YOU GETTING HURT?

06:53.542 --> 06:55.667
WELL, IF I'M GONNA HAVE
A HEART ATTACK AND DIE,

06:55.750 --> 06:57.166
IT MAY AS WELL
BE DURING SEX.

06:57.250 --> 06:58.250
THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEANT.

06:58.333 --> 06:59.709
OKAY, FINE. WHATEVER.

06:59.792 --> 07:01.291
I'LL TAKE A VOW OF CHASTITY.
ARE YOU HAPPY?

07:01.375 --> 07:02.834
LISTEN, I KNOW YOU DON'T WANT
TO HEAR THIS,

07:02.917 --> 07:05.083
BUT YOU AND HUNTER --

07:05.166 --> 07:09.291
YOU SHOULD NOT...BE.

07:11.166 --> 07:13.166
IT'S FOR YOUR OWN GOOD.

07:15.333 --> 07:17.834
[ SIGHS ]

07:20.834 --> 07:22.917
I SWEAR
I'VE NEVER FELT BETTER.

07:23.000 --> 07:24.458
AND YOUR JOURNAL?

07:24.542 --> 07:26.125
YOU'VE STOPPED WRITING DOWN
YOUR FOOD INTAKE.

07:26.208 --> 07:28.917
NOT COMPLETELY, BUT IT'S NOT
AS INTENSE AS IT USED TO BE.

07:29.000 --> 07:31.250
LIKE, THE OTHER DAY,
A BUNCH OF US WENT OUT,

07:31.333 --> 07:33.125
AND WE ATE
ALL THIS JUNK FOOD --

07:33.208 --> 07:35.500
YOU KNOW, CHIPS AND HOT DOGS
AND EVERYTHING.

07:35.583 --> 07:36.959
AND YOU PARTICIPATED?

07:37.041 --> 07:39.458
IT'S BEEN EASIER
TO PARTICIPATE LATELY.

07:39.542 --> 07:41.709
AND AFTER YOU ATE
WITH EVERYBODY,

07:41.792 --> 07:43.500
HOW DID THAT MAKE YOU FEEL?

07:46.417 --> 07:48.083
[ CLATTER ]

07:48.166 --> 07:49.333
GREAT!

07:49.417 --> 07:51.041
I FELT REALLY STRONG.

07:51.125 --> 07:52.083
[ GRUNTS ]

07:52.166 --> 07:53.625
NOBODY'S BODY IS PERFECT.

07:53.709 --> 07:54.917
THREE MORE.
YOU GOT THIS.

07:55.000 --> 07:56.291
Emma:
THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

07:56.375 --> 07:58.250
OUR BODIES ARE MEANT
TO FUNCTION --

07:58.333 --> 07:59.709
WALKING, LIFTING,

07:59.792 --> 08:01.166
MOVING US
THROUGH THE WORLD.

08:01.250 --> 08:02.875
THAT IS WHAT OUR BODIES
ARE ACTUALLY FOR.

08:02.959 --> 08:04.959
AND I AM BEGINNING
TO UNDERSTAND

08:05.041 --> 08:07.875
THAT IT'S NOT TO BE THIN
OR TO LOOK A CERTAIN WAY.

08:07.959 --> 08:10.500
THE MOST IMPORTANT THING
IS TO BE HEALTHY

08:10.583 --> 08:12.166
AND TO LISTEN
TO YOUR BODY.

08:12.250 --> 08:13.625
AND WHEN YOU HAVE
A SETBACK?

08:13.709 --> 08:15.625
[ GROANS ]

08:15.709 --> 08:17.208
GOOD. IF YOU'RE GONNA FALL,
THAT'S HOW YOU DO IT.

08:17.291 --> 08:20.041
Emma:
WHAT DO YOU MEAN BY SETBACK?

08:20.125 --> 08:21.875
EMMA,
WHEN YOU FIRST GOT HERE,

08:21.959 --> 08:24.667
YOU THOUGHT THAT IF YOU ATE
SOMETHING BAD, YOU <i>WERE</i> BAD.

08:24.750 --> 08:27.083
YOU WERE A FAILURE.
YOU THOUGHT YOU WERE DOOMED.

08:27.166 --> 08:28.542
YES.

08:28.625 --> 08:30.709
AND I'VE LEARNED
THAT THAT'S NOT TRUE.

08:30.792 --> 08:32.166
FOOD IS NOT THE ENEMY.

08:32.250 --> 08:33.667
IT IS A VITAL PART OF LIFE,

08:33.750 --> 08:35.500
AND WE NEED IT
TO STAY ALIVE.

08:35.583 --> 08:37.166
DO YOU THINK
YOU CAN SUSTAIN

08:37.250 --> 08:39.333
THAT KIND OF THINKING
IF YOU WERE HOME?

08:39.417 --> 08:41.208
HOME?

08:41.291 --> 08:43.208
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
YOU'RE -- YOU'RE JOKING, RIGHT?

08:43.291 --> 08:45.083
YOU'RE SAYING I COULD ACTUALLY
GO HOME EARLY?

08:45.166 --> 08:46.375
WELL, THERE'S A PROCESS.

08:46.458 --> 08:47.625
WE'VE GOT TO TALK
TO THE DOCTORS,

08:47.709 --> 08:49.250
GET THEIR INPUT,

08:49.333 --> 08:51.166
BUT YOU'VE BEEN CANCER FREE
FOR EIGHT WEEKS NOW,

08:51.250 --> 08:52.750
AND YOU'RE AT LEAST
A WEEK AHEAD

08:52.834 --> 08:54.000
OF WHERE I THOUGHT YOU'D BE
WITH THE PROSTHETIC.

08:54.083 --> 08:56.417
Emma: IT'S JUST, UH...

08:56.500 --> 08:59.125
IT'S -- IT'S KIND OF IMPOSSIBLE
TO BELIEVE, YOU KNOW,

08:59.208 --> 09:01.333
THAT I'M ACTUALLY WELL ENOUGH
TO GO HOME.

09:01.417 --> 09:04.250
EMMA,
THE NUMBERS DON'T LIE.

09:04.333 --> 09:07.125
YOUR BODY TEMPERATURE
IS ALMOST NORMAL AT 98.1,

09:07.208 --> 09:09.542
YOUR DAYTIME HEART RATE
IS IN THE 60s,

09:09.625 --> 09:12.875
AND YOU'RE JUST HALF A POUND
AWAY FROM YOUR GOAL WEIGHT.

09:12.959 --> 09:14.417
THAT'S PRETTY IMPRESSIVE

09:14.500 --> 09:16.792
FOR A YOUNG LADY WHO WALKED
IN HERE AT 83 POUNDS.

09:16.875 --> 09:20.125
I'D HAVE TO RUN IT BY THE REST
OF THE STAFF, OF COURSE, BUT --

09:20.208 --> 09:21.375
BUT IF THEY AGREE?

09:21.458 --> 09:23.291
YOU'LL BE PACKING
YOUR BAGS.

09:23.375 --> 09:26.542
HOW DOES THAT
MAKE YOU FEEL, EMMA?

09:26.625 --> 09:28.583
GREAT. [ CHUCKLES ]

09:28.667 --> 09:30.625
IT MAKES ME FEEL GREAT.

09:39.125 --> 09:40.250
Delaney:
♪ ALREADY GOT ENOUGH ♪

09:40.333 --> 09:42.834
♪ I WENT DOWN BY THE OCEAN ♪

09:42.917 --> 09:45.792
♪ BEEN THROUGH WAVES
OF EMOTION ♪

09:45.875 --> 09:48.458
♪ THEY TRY TO SELL ME
ALL THESE THINGS ♪

09:48.542 --> 09:51.000
♪ BUT LOVE IS REALLY
ALL I NEED ♪

09:51.083 --> 09:54.250
♪ I DON'T KNOW WHAT
THEY'RE FUSSING 'BOUT ♪

09:54.333 --> 09:56.458
♪ I DON'T CARE WHAT
THEY TALKING 'BOUT ♪

09:56.542 --> 09:59.667
♪ EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE OKAY ♪

09:59.750 --> 10:02.375
♪ EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE OKAY ♪

10:02.458 --> 10:04.750
♪ I DON'T KNOW WHAT
THEY'RE WAITING FOR ♪

10:04.834 --> 10:06.375
DO YOU SEE WHAT I'M SEEING?

10:06.458 --> 10:07.875
♪ I KNOW THERE'S GOT TO BE
SOMETHING MORE ♪

10:07.959 --> 10:09.667
OH, COME ON.
I MEAN, GIVE HIM A BREAK.

10:09.750 --> 10:12.291
BOYS HIS AGE -- THEY NEED --
THEY NEED PRACTICE WITH GIRLS.

10:12.375 --> 10:16.166
MM. SOME OF THEM
STILL NEED IT IN THEIR 30s,

10:16.250 --> 10:18.667
EVEN PAST THE POINT
WHERE THEY'RE OLD AND GRAY.

10:18.750 --> 10:20.667
PREMATURELY GRAY.
♪ EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE OKAY ♪

10:20.750 --> 10:22.583
POINT TAKEN.

10:22.667 --> 10:26.041
LISTEN, I-I KNOW I DON'T HAVE
THE BEST TRACK RECORD

10:26.125 --> 10:27.583
WHEN IT COMES TO WOMEN.

10:27.667 --> 10:29.458
BUT GUESS WHAT --
I'M READY TO MAKE A CHANGE.

10:29.542 --> 10:31.333
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHERE THIS IS GOING,

10:31.417 --> 10:33.041
BUT IT CAN'T POSSIBLY
BE GOOD.

10:33.125 --> 10:36.625
I'M THINKING ABOUT GETTING BACK
TOGETHER WITH ERIN.

10:36.709 --> 10:40.291
DOES STUPIDITY
RUN IN YOUR FAMILY?

10:40.375 --> 10:43.500
I'LL TAKE THAT
AS YOUR BLESSING.

10:43.583 --> 10:45.417
DO YOU REALIZE
BY THE END OF THE WEEK,

10:45.500 --> 10:47.917
WE COULD BOTH BE BACK HOME,
SLEEPING IN OUR OWN BEDS,

10:48.000 --> 10:49.291
GETTING
OUR REAL LIVES BACK?

10:49.375 --> 10:51.125
I KNOW.
IT'S ALL HAPPENING SO QUICKLY.

10:51.208 --> 10:53.291
[ SIREN WAILS ]
YOU'RE NOT PSYCHED?

10:53.375 --> 10:55.208
I'M JUST STILL PROCESSING.

10:55.291 --> 10:57.083
TO GET MY HOPES UP

10:57.166 --> 10:59.625
THAT I <i>DON'T</i> GET OUT, SO --

10:59.709 --> 11:02.083
YOU WILL.
WE BOTH WILL.

11:02.166 --> 11:03.709
DO YOU HAVE
A CRYSTAL BALL?

11:03.792 --> 11:05.458
I HAVE A DELUDED
SENSE OF CONFIDENCE.

11:05.542 --> 11:08.834
MY PHYSICAL THERAPIST SAYS
IT'S THE SECRET TO MY SUCCESS.

11:08.917 --> 11:10.333
HEY, YOU OKAY?

11:10.417 --> 11:11.667
YES.

11:11.750 --> 11:13.834
REALLY?
WHAT AREN'T YOU TELLING ME?

11:13.917 --> 11:15.166
NOTHING.

11:15.250 --> 11:18.542
OH, MY GOD.

11:18.625 --> 11:20.417
EMMA, WE'RE NOT GONNA BREAK UP
WHEN WE GET OUT OF HERE.

11:20.500 --> 11:22.500
I MEAN, IT COULD HAPPEN.

11:22.583 --> 11:24.041
NO, IT WON'T.

11:24.125 --> 11:26.333
IT'S REALLY NOT THAT FAR
FROM L.A. TO BAKERSFIELD.

11:26.417 --> 11:29.792
YOU KNOW, WE'RE GONNA
FIGURE IT OUT, I PROMISE.

11:44.083 --> 11:47.208
OLD MAN RIVER SEEMS LIKE
A GOOD PROSPECT.

11:47.291 --> 11:48.917
A PROSPECT FOR WHAT?

11:54.166 --> 11:57.542
NURSE JACKSON NEEDS A HEARTBEAT,
SHE CAN HAVE THIS ONE.

12:02.500 --> 12:03.625
AND THIS WILL BUY US
HOW MUCH TIME?

12:03.709 --> 12:05.125
AS MUCH AS YOU NEED.

12:07.125 --> 12:08.792
[ BELL DINGS ]

12:08.875 --> 12:10.417
<i>I SURE HOPE OLD MAN RIVER</i>
<i>CAN KEEP A SECRET.</i>

12:18.250 --> 12:21.375
WAIT.
YOU BROUGHT A CONDOM, RIGHT?

12:23.125 --> 12:24.250
I'LL FIND ONE.

12:24.333 --> 12:25.792
I'M ALL OVER IT.

12:27.792 --> 12:30.709
SURE, UH...
HEALTHY CHOICES THERE.

12:30.792 --> 12:32.041
[ LAUGHS ]

12:32.125 --> 12:33.500
WAIT, ARE THOSE ANCHOVIES?

12:33.583 --> 12:34.750
HIGH IN OMEGA-3s.

12:34.834 --> 12:36.250
SO YOU'VE BEEN LYING TO ME

12:36.333 --> 12:38.041
ABOUT YOUR PIZZA PREFERENCE
THIS WHOLE TIME?

12:38.125 --> 12:40.917
[ LAUGHS ]
I STARTED EATING THEM IN AFRICA.

12:41.000 --> 12:42.875
SARDINES, ACTUALLY,
BUT, YOU KNOW, SAME THING.

12:42.959 --> 12:45.041
MY MOM WAS WORRIED I WASN'T
GETTING ENOUGH PROTEIN,

12:45.125 --> 12:47.083
SO SHE WOULD SEND ME
THESE MONTHLY CARE PACKAGES,

12:47.166 --> 12:48.500
AND THEY TRAVEL WELL,

12:48.583 --> 12:49.834
BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,
THEY'RE PACKED LIKE --

12:49.917 --> 12:51.542
LIKE SARDINES.
LIKE SARDINES.

12:51.625 --> 12:52.417
THAT'S VERY FUNNY, ERIN.

12:52.500 --> 12:54.000
THERE YOU ARE.

12:54.083 --> 12:55.667
I ACCIDENTALLY TOOK YOUR KEYS
THIS MORNING.

12:55.750 --> 12:57.959
OH, HI.
HI.

12:58.041 --> 12:59.208
SORRY, MAN.
I DIDN'T MEAN TO CUT IN LINE.

12:59.291 --> 13:00.583
OH.

13:00.667 --> 13:02.625
UM, SAM, ADAM.
ADAM, SAM.

13:02.709 --> 13:04.041
UH...
NICE TO MEET YOU.

13:04.125 --> 13:05.458
THAT'S A HELL
OF A HANDSHAKE.

13:05.542 --> 13:06.667
ADAM IS A WORK COLLEAGUE.

13:06.750 --> 13:08.083
WE WENT TO
MED SCHOOL TOGETHER.

13:08.166 --> 13:09.542
AND HE'S ONE OF THE BEST

13:09.625 --> 13:11.333
PEDIATRIC SURGEONS
IN THE COUNTRY.

13:11.417 --> 13:12.500
WOW.

13:12.583 --> 13:14.417
IMPRESSIVE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:14.500 --> 13:16.041
SAM AND I MET IN SENEGAL.

13:16.125 --> 13:18.208
HE WORKS FOR THE I.R.C.
ON CLEAN-WATER ISSUES.

13:18.291 --> 13:20.792
ALSO IMPRESSIVE.

13:20.875 --> 13:23.208
YOU LIVE HERE NOW IN L.A.?

13:23.291 --> 13:25.125
I'M, UM, THINKING ABOUT IT.

13:25.208 --> 13:27.959
I'M STAYING WITH ERIN
IN BETWEEN GIGS,

13:28.041 --> 13:30.625
BUT IT CERTAINLY FEELS LIKE
A PLACE I CAN GET USED TO.

13:30.709 --> 13:31.959
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:32.041 --> 13:34.667
WELL, THAT'S GREAT.
EXCUSE ME.

13:34.750 --> 13:36.041
I'M -- I'M SO SORRY.

13:36.125 --> 13:37.750
YOU KNOW, I-I HAVE ROUNDS,
AND, UH,

13:37.834 --> 13:40.792
UM, I'LL LEAVE YOU THIS
FOR THE BANANA. THANK YOU.

13:40.875 --> 13:43.166
UM, NICE TO MEET YOU.

13:43.250 --> 13:47.125
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY OUT.
GET OUT!

13:47.208 --> 13:48.375
GO, GO! LET'S GO!

13:50.125 --> 13:51.041
EXCEPT YOU.

13:51.125 --> 13:53.625
COME HERE.

13:53.709 --> 13:55.166
WHY DON'T I KNOW YOU?

13:55.250 --> 13:58.250
WELL, I'M "DASH" HOSNEY,

13:58.333 --> 14:01.500
UH, OCEAN PARK
HOSPITALITY LIAISON.

14:01.583 --> 14:04.166
AND IF I MAY SAY UP CLOSE
AND PERSONAL LIKE THIS,

14:04.250 --> 14:07.208
YOU DO NOT LOOK EXHAUSTED
AT ALL.

14:07.291 --> 14:09.500
YOU LOOK DAMN FINE.

14:09.583 --> 14:13.333
SO, WHAT ARE YOU IN FOR?

14:13.417 --> 14:14.709
HERE.

14:14.792 --> 14:16.250
WELL, UH, I HAVE A...

14:16.333 --> 14:20.500
A NONCONTAGIOUS,
YET LIFE-THREATENING DISEASE.

14:20.583 --> 14:23.875
SO, YOU'RE DYING?

14:23.959 --> 14:25.500
EVEN WORSE.

14:25.583 --> 14:30.333
I'M DYING WITHOUT EVER
FULLY EXPERIENCING THE RAPTURE

14:30.417 --> 14:32.000
THAT COMES FROM HAVING SEX

14:32.083 --> 14:34.917
WITH ONE OF <i>PEOPLE'S</i>
MOST BEAUTIFUL PEOPLE.

14:38.417 --> 14:41.041
[ Laughing ] OH, MY GOD!

14:41.125 --> 14:42.542
[ LAUGHS ]

14:42.625 --> 14:44.917
THAT WAS <i>SO</i> LAME.
[ LAUGHS ]

14:45.000 --> 14:47.959
OKAY, I AM NOT ABOUT
TO WASTE MY VAJAZZLING

14:48.041 --> 14:50.250
ON THE MAKE-A-WISH
FOUNDATION.

14:50.333 --> 14:52.709
IS THAT A YES OR A NO?

14:52.792 --> 14:55.291
I HAVEN'T DECIDED YET.

14:55.375 --> 14:56.792
TAKE OFF YOUR SHIRT.

14:56.875 --> 14:58.792
LET ME SEE THE GOODS.
[ EXHALES SLOWLY ]

15:01.083 --> 15:02.667
UH, EXCUSE ME.
MS. SHAW?

15:02.750 --> 15:04.959
NOBODY'S HOME RIGHT NOW.
CAN YOU COME BACK LATER, PLEASE?

15:05.041 --> 15:06.542
UH, MY NAME
IS JORDI PALACIOS.

15:06.625 --> 15:08.500
I WAS WONDERING
IF YOU'D BE COMFORTABLE

15:08.583 --> 15:10.792
INTRODUCING ME TO YOUR MANAGER,
BRIAN KAVANAUGH.

15:10.875 --> 15:11.959
I'M A SINGER/SONGWRITER.

15:12.041 --> 15:13.875
ARE YOU DYING, TOO?

15:13.959 --> 15:15.959
I AM PRETTY FULL OF CANCER
AT THE MOMENT.

15:16.041 --> 15:18.834
FASCINATING.

15:18.917 --> 15:21.166
LET ME THINK ABOUT THIS
FOR A MOMENT.

15:21.250 --> 15:23.917
OKAY.

15:24.000 --> 15:27.000
I WILL GIVE YOU 10 MINUTES
WITH MY MANAGER.

15:27.083 --> 15:28.083
SERIOUSLY?

15:28.166 --> 15:29.250
FOR 10 PAINKILLERS.

15:29.333 --> 15:30.333
PAINKILLERS?

15:30.417 --> 15:31.792
PAINKILLERS, YES --

15:31.875 --> 15:33.166
MUSCLE RELAXERS,
SEROTONIN INHIBITORS.

15:33.250 --> 15:34.417
I'M REALLY NOT PICKY, SO --

15:34.500 --> 15:35.709
NO, IT'S NOT THAT.

15:35.792 --> 15:37.625
IT'S JUST THEY DON'T
GIVE ME THAT.

15:37.709 --> 15:40.458
THEY ONLY GIVE IT TO YOU
WHEN YOU REALLY NEED IT.

15:40.542 --> 15:43.375
OH. WELL...

15:43.458 --> 15:45.417
<i>I</i> REALLY NEED IT,

15:45.500 --> 15:50.750
AND <i>YOU</i> REALLY NEED 10 MINUTES
WITH MY MANAGER.

15:50.834 --> 15:53.709
I'M SURE
YOU'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

15:53.792 --> 15:56.083
I'M TIRED NOW.
YOU BOYS CAN GO.

15:56.166 --> 15:57.959
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT ABOUT THE --

15:58.041 --> 16:00.333
NIGHT-NIGHT.

16:05.959 --> 16:07.709
[ THE WEALTHY WEST'S
"ALL I NEED" PLAYS ]

16:12.583 --> 16:18.959
♪ I WOKE UP
TO THE MORNING LIGHT ♪

16:19.041 --> 16:25.500
♪ AND I SEE THE SUN
IS SHINING BRIGHT ♪

16:25.583 --> 16:30.500
♪ AND ALL THE CLOUDS, WELL,
THEY'RE STARTING TO DISAPPEAR ♪

16:30.583 --> 16:33.041
10 MINUTES WITH ONE OF
THE BIGGEST MANAGERS OUT THERE.

16:33.125 --> 16:34.667
I KNOW I CAN
BLOW THIS GUY AWAY.

16:34.750 --> 16:37.291
TOO BAD IT'S ILLEGAL
TO SELL PHARMACEUTICALS.

16:37.375 --> 16:38.792
YOU AND LEO GET PEOPLE DRUGS
ALL THE TIME.

16:38.875 --> 16:40.125
MEDICAL MARIJUANA
IS A DIFFERENT STORY.

16:40.208 --> 16:41.625
[ SIGHS ]
KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?

16:41.709 --> 16:43.291
I'M NOT MESSING AROUND
WITH NO 'SCRIPS.

16:43.375 --> 16:45.417
LOOK, JORDI, I KNOW YOU WANT
TO BE A SINGER AND ALL THAT.

16:45.500 --> 16:46.834
NO, I-I DON'T <i>WANT</i>
TO BE A SINGER.

16:46.917 --> 16:48.166
I <i>NEED</i> TO BE A SINGER.

16:48.250 --> 16:50.000
THIS COULD SOLVE
ALL MY PROBLEMS.

16:50.083 --> 16:51.667
THIS IS MY WAY IN.

16:51.750 --> 16:53.166
THE MUSIC HAS ALWAYS
BEEN MY DREAM,

16:53.250 --> 16:54.709
AND NOW I JUST HAPPEN TO BE
IN THE SAME HOSPITAL

16:54.792 --> 16:56.375
WITH ONE OF THE BIGGEST
POP STARS IN THE WORLD?

16:56.458 --> 16:58.333
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S AN ACCIDENT.
JORDI --

16:58.417 --> 17:01.709
NO, MAYBE THAT'S THE REASON I
GOT CANCER IN THE FIRST PLACE --

17:01.792 --> 17:05.542
SO MY DREAM
COULD FINALLY COME TRUE.

17:05.625 --> 17:08.333
WOULDN'T <i>THAT</i> BE SOMETHING?

17:09.750 --> 17:11.959
OH, HI.

17:12.041 --> 17:14.875
CAREFUL.
I THINK THAT'S DECAF.

17:20.291 --> 17:21.875
IS SOMETHING WRONG?

17:23.750 --> 17:25.333
WHAT COULD
POSSIBLY BE WRONG?

17:26.709 --> 17:28.291
YOUR TONE.

17:28.375 --> 17:30.667
YOUR TONE IS DEFINITELY IMPLYING
THAT SOMETHING IS WRONG.

17:30.750 --> 17:32.834
I MEAN, ADMITTEDLY,
IT'S NOT AS -- AS SWEET

17:32.917 --> 17:35.709
AS "I MISS YOU, ADAM,"
AND THEN TOUCHING MY ARM.

17:35.792 --> 17:37.583
I NEVER TOUCHED YOUR ARM.

17:37.667 --> 17:39.125
YEAH, YOU DID,

17:39.208 --> 17:41.583
AND THEN YOU BLINDSIDED ME
WITH, UH, YOSEMITE SAM.

17:41.667 --> 17:43.208
I DID NOT!

17:43.291 --> 17:44.959
I MEAN, PARADING
YOUR NEW BOYFRIEND

17:45.041 --> 17:47.500
IN FRONT OF YOUR OLD BOYFRIEND
JUST TO MAKE HIM JEALOUS?

17:47.583 --> 17:49.291
THAT'S, UH --
THAT SEEMS BENEATH YOU.

17:49.375 --> 17:52.709
WOW. I AM SURPRISED.

17:52.792 --> 17:54.458
BUT MAYBE I SHOULDN'T BE,

17:54.542 --> 17:57.041
BECAUSE THIS IS YOU,
THE REAL YOU,

17:57.125 --> 17:58.667
CHILDISH,
COMPLETELY FULL OF YOURSELF.

17:58.750 --> 18:00.166
WHAT DOES <i>THAT</i> MEAN?

18:00.250 --> 18:02.375
IT MEANS THAT <i>YOU</i>
BROKE UP WITH <i>ME!</i>

18:02.458 --> 18:04.625
OH.
DO YOU REMEMBER THAT?!

18:04.709 --> 18:06.291
DOES THAT RING ANY BELLS
FOR YOU?

18:06.375 --> 18:08.291
AND IT TOOK ME AN ENTIRE YEAR
TO GET OVER YOU,

18:08.375 --> 18:10.750
A YEAR OF LIVING IN AFRICA
IN FAMINE AND DISEASE.

18:10.834 --> 18:13.417
AND NOW I'M SUPPOSED TO FEEL BAD
ABOUT MOVING ON?

18:13.500 --> 18:15.083
COME ON.

18:15.166 --> 18:16.917
I MEAN, YOU ARE REALLY GOOD
AT WORKING WITH KIDS,

18:17.000 --> 18:18.667
BUT IT'S BECAUSE YOU DON'T WANT
TO GROW UP

18:18.750 --> 18:20.834
AND YOU DON'T WANT
TO BE COMMITTED TO
ANYBODY OR ANYTHING.

18:20.917 --> 18:23.000
I-I DON'T WANT
TO BE COMMITTED?
NO.

18:23.083 --> 18:25.250
UM, WHO'S THE ONE
THAT WENT TO AFRICA?

18:25.333 --> 18:27.166
UM --
I'M STILL HERE.

18:27.250 --> 18:29.000
I HAVEN'T LEFT!

18:29.083 --> 18:30.250
WHAT WAS I SUPPOSED TO DO,

18:30.333 --> 18:31.625
PACK UP ALL MY STUFF
AND GO WITH YOU?

18:31.709 --> 18:33.417
YEAH, BECAUSE NO GUY
WOULD EVER DO THAT.

18:33.500 --> 18:36.083
OH, DON'T --
INSTEAD, I NEED TO GIVE UP
ON MY DREAMS

18:36.166 --> 18:38.417
FOR THE INCREDIBLE HONOR
OF BEING IN A RELATIONSHIP

18:38.500 --> 18:40.000
WITH YOU ON FACEBOOK
THREE YEARS.

18:40.083 --> 18:41.834
THREE YEARS
WE WERE TOGETHER,

18:41.917 --> 18:43.583
AND NOT ONE TIME DID YOU EVER
MENTION MARRIAGE --

18:43.667 --> 18:45.917
WHICH, BY THE WAY,
IT'S TOTALLY FINE WITH ME,

18:46.000 --> 18:49.458
BECAUSE...IT'S JUST NOT
WHO YOU ARE,

18:49.542 --> 18:51.959
IS IT?

18:52.041 --> 18:54.709
LESSON LEARNED.

19:01.542 --> 19:04.709
<i>WHAT YOU'RE WITNESSING HERE</i>
<i>IS A HEIST.</i>

19:04.792 --> 19:07.625
<i>STEP ONE --</i>
<i>LOOK FOR AN EASY MARK.</i>

19:07.709 --> 19:11.083
<i>NOPE.</i>
<i>KID'S GOT A BODYGUARD.</i>

19:19.375 --> 19:22.125
<i>JACKPOT!</i>

19:22.208 --> 19:23.792
HI, MS. RIVKIN.
IT'S REALLY COMING ALONG.

19:23.875 --> 19:24.959
OH, HEY, KIDDO.

19:25.041 --> 19:27.041
CRAZY, HUH?

19:27.125 --> 19:29.542
I TOLD MY DAUGHTER
I'D QUIT CROCHETING

19:29.625 --> 19:32.375
WHEN THE CANCER QUITS ME...
OR I CROAK.

19:32.458 --> 19:33.667
<i>NEXT, EARN THE MARK'S TRUST.</i>

19:33.750 --> 19:35.208
HOW ARE THE GRANDKIDS?

19:35.291 --> 19:36.667
WASN'T LITTLE SALLY
ABOUT TO LOSE A TOOTH?

19:36.750 --> 19:39.333
OH, AREN'T YOU SWEET
FOR ALWAYS ASKING?

19:39.417 --> 19:42.000
[ GASPS ]
BE A DEAR AND GRAB MY PHONE.

19:42.083 --> 19:43.333
I'VE GOT ANOTHER PICTURE
IN THERE.

19:43.417 --> 19:44.834
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:44.917 --> 19:47.709
<i>STEP THREE --</i>
<i>EXECUTE THE PLAN.</i>

19:47.792 --> 19:51.500
JORDI.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

19:51.583 --> 19:54.083
UH, GETTING CHEMO.

19:54.166 --> 19:55.667
YOU'RE DONE
WITH YOUR FIRST ROUND.

19:55.750 --> 19:57.834
YOUR SECOND ROUND'S NOT
SCHEDULED TILL NEXT WEEK.

19:57.917 --> 20:00.083
OH. THOUGHT IT WAS TODAY.
MUST BE MY CHEMO BRAIN.

20:02.542 --> 20:03.917
BYE, MS. RIVKIN.

20:04.000 --> 20:05.667
BYE, HONEY.

20:05.750 --> 20:09.166
<i>OH, AND DID I FORGET</i>
<i>TO MENTION,</i>

20:09.250 --> 20:11.291
<i>MAKE A FAST GETAWAY?</i>

20:11.375 --> 20:13.959
<i>GUESS WHEN YOU SPEND</i>
<i>YOUR CHILDHOOD</i>

20:14.041 --> 20:15.750
<i>IN BACKROOM POKER GAMES,</i>

20:15.834 --> 20:18.959
<i>HUSTLING COMES AS NATURALLY</i>
<i>AS RIDING A BIKE.</i>

20:19.041 --> 20:22.125
<i>YOU NEVER FORGET HOW.</i>

20:24.917 --> 20:26.542
I NEED A CONDOM.

20:26.625 --> 20:27.750
EXCUSE ME?

20:27.834 --> 20:30.542
A CONDOM,
A PROPHYLACTIC.

20:30.625 --> 20:32.208
IT'S A FORM
OF BIRTH CONTROL,

20:32.291 --> 20:34.208
KIND OF LIKE THE DRESS
YOU'RE HOLDING UP.

20:34.291 --> 20:35.458
I DON'T HAVE ANY CONDOMS.

20:35.542 --> 20:36.959
OH, MY GOD, PLEASE.

20:37.041 --> 20:38.333
YOU AND LEO <i>MUST</i>
BE DOING IT BY NOW.

20:38.417 --> 20:39.875
YOU'VE BEEN TOGETHER
FOREVER.

20:39.959 --> 20:42.125
YOU AND I CLEARLY HAVE
A DIFFERENT DEFINITION

20:42.208 --> 20:43.709
OF THE WORD "FOREVER"

20:43.792 --> 20:46.250
AND VERY DIFFERENT IDEAS
ABOUT SEX, I WOULD IMAGINE.

20:46.333 --> 20:47.834
OKAY, SEX IS NOT AN IDEA.

20:47.917 --> 20:49.709
IT'S SOMETHING YOU DO
WHEN YOU LIKE SOMEONE.

20:49.792 --> 20:52.166
NO, IT'S SOMETHING <i>YOU</i> DO WHEN
YOU'RE ATTRACTED TO SOMEONE.

20:52.250 --> 20:53.542
SAME DIFF.

20:53.625 --> 20:55.667
ATTRACTION AND LOVE
ARE NOT THE SAME.

20:55.750 --> 20:57.250
EVEN YOU'RE NOT THAT STUPID.

20:57.333 --> 20:58.583
AND YOU'RE NOT THAT NAIVE.

20:58.667 --> 21:00.250
YOU DON'T NEED TO BE IN LOVE
TO HAVE SEX.

21:00.333 --> 21:01.917
YOU JUST NEED A CONDOM.

21:02.000 --> 21:03.375
SO, DO YOU HAVE ONE OR NOT?

21:03.458 --> 21:05.000
I REALLY DON'T GET YOU.

21:05.083 --> 21:06.917
MOST GIRLS HAVE SEX TOO SOON
BECAUSE THEY'RE INSECURE.

21:07.000 --> 21:09.709
BUT YOU -- YOU SEEM TO HAVE
THE OPPOSITE PROBLEM --

21:09.792 --> 21:11.083
TOO MUCH SELF-ESTEEM.

21:11.166 --> 21:14.417
WELL, AWESOMENESS
IS MY CROSS TO BEAR.

21:14.500 --> 21:15.542
SO, THEN, WHAT ARE YOU
TRYING TO PROVE

21:15.625 --> 21:16.417
SO DESPERATELY WITH HUNTER?

21:18.000 --> 21:20.166
OR ARE YOU AFRAID
THAT IF YOU WAIT TOO LONG,

21:20.250 --> 21:22.250
HE'LL REALIZE HOW HORRIBLE
YOU TRULY ARE

21:22.333 --> 21:24.083
AND NEVER WANT TO HAVE SEX
WITH YOU?

21:24.166 --> 21:26.000
OH, <i>I'M</i> NOT THE ONE
WHO'S DESPERATE.

21:26.083 --> 21:27.750
HAVE YOU SEEN YOURSELF
WITH LEO?

21:27.834 --> 21:28.709
WHAT IS THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

21:28.792 --> 21:30.208
WHENEVER HE'S AROUND,

21:30.291 --> 21:32.166
YOU'RE ALWAYS TRYING TO HIDE
YOUR WEIRD REXINESS,

21:32.250 --> 21:33.959
TRYING TO PASS OFF
AS NORMAL.

21:34.041 --> 21:35.542
[ CHUCKLES ] NEWS FLASH --

21:35.625 --> 21:38.750
A NORMAL TEENAGER
WOULD BE DOING IT BY NOW.

21:38.834 --> 21:40.500
YEAH, WELL,
A REAL RELATIONSHIP

21:40.583 --> 21:43.417
IS ABOUT GETTING TO KNOW SOMEONE
ON A LEVEL DEEPER THAN SEX.

21:43.500 --> 21:44.875
REAL RELATIONSHIPS?

21:44.959 --> 21:46.625
YOU MEAN THE KIND
WHERE YOU BARE YOUR SOUL

21:46.709 --> 21:49.166
TO THE OTHER PERSON
AND LET THEM SEE THE REAL YOU?

21:49.250 --> 21:51.959
GO AHEAD,
SLUT-SHAME ME ALL YOU WANT.

21:52.041 --> 21:54.166
BUT I'M NOT THE ONE LYING
TO MY SO-CALLED BOYFRIEND

21:54.250 --> 21:55.375
ON A DAILY BASIS.

21:56.917 --> 22:00.041
HOW REAL CAN YOUR RELATIONSHIP
BE IF IT'S BASED ON A LIE?

22:06.333 --> 22:09.375
SO, YOUR KIDS
ARE IN COLLEGE?

22:09.458 --> 22:10.583
UH-HUH.
WOW.

22:10.667 --> 22:12.125
[ CHUCKLES ]
THAT'S GREAT.

22:12.208 --> 22:13.959
IT'S A LOT OF FREEDOM.
OH, YEAH.

22:14.041 --> 22:16.834
MY WIFE AND I -- WELL [CHUCKLES]
MY FIRST WIFE...

22:16.917 --> 22:18.250
[ LAUGHS ]
MM!

22:18.333 --> 22:20.458
...STARTED YOUNG.
OH, YEAH.

22:20.542 --> 22:23.250
SO H-HOW MANY WIVES DO YOU
HAVE -- OR HAVE YOU HAD?

22:23.333 --> 22:24.917
UNLESS YOU'RE
STILL...MARRIED?

22:25.000 --> 22:26.750
WHAT WAS THAT?

22:26.834 --> 22:28.500
UH, NOTHING.

22:37.583 --> 22:39.458
BRITTANY.
OH, HI.

22:39.542 --> 22:40.792
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

22:40.875 --> 22:42.917
ARE YOU DRINKING?

22:43.000 --> 22:44.542
UM...

22:44.625 --> 22:46.750
I MEAN, THAT'S -- THAT'S --
THAT'S PRETTY CARELESS

22:46.834 --> 22:48.250
WHEN YOU'RE CARRYING
OUR BABY.

22:48.333 --> 22:49.834
Y-YOUR WHAT?

22:49.917 --> 22:52.583
HIS BABY.

22:52.667 --> 22:54.083
I'M A SURROGATE.

22:54.166 --> 22:56.000
THAT'S RIGHT.
MM, YES.

22:56.083 --> 22:58.041
YEAH.
HE'S GAY.

22:58.125 --> 23:01.792
OH.
YES. HE AND HIS PARTNER,
ALAN,

23:01.875 --> 23:04.250
WERE WAITING ON AN ADOPTION
TO GO THROUGH LAST YEAR,

23:04.333 --> 23:06.250
AND IT FELL THROUGH
AT THE LAST MINUTE.

23:06.333 --> 23:08.458
AND THEIR STORY WAS JUST
SO HEARTBREAKING,

23:08.542 --> 23:10.542
I COULDN'T SAY NO,

23:10.625 --> 23:14.417
ESPECIALLY SINCE ALAN AND I
USED TO BE COLLEGE SWEETHEARTS.

23:14.500 --> 23:16.125
ALAN IS BI.

23:16.208 --> 23:19.125
HE'S A BISEXUAL.
OKAY, UM...

23:19.208 --> 23:21.875
I'M -- I'M GONNA LET YOU TWO
GUYS WORK THIS OUT.

23:21.959 --> 23:23.291
UM...
YEAH, THAT'S OKAY.
THANK YOU.

23:23.375 --> 23:24.458
YEAH, NICE MEETING YOU.

23:24.542 --> 23:25.834
YOU TOO. YEAH.

23:25.917 --> 23:27.625
I'M VERY SORRY.
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

23:27.709 --> 23:28.792
GOOD LUCK. YEAH, SURE.

23:28.875 --> 23:29.959
OH.
YEAH.
YEAH. THANKS.

23:30.041 --> 23:31.250
[ LAUGHS ]

23:31.333 --> 23:33.417
THAT -- THAT STORY
WAS INCREDIBLE.

23:33.500 --> 23:34.750
[ Chuckling ] OH, NO.

23:34.834 --> 23:35.959
THANK YOU FOR SAVING ME.

23:36.041 --> 23:37.625
NO. YOU DID
THE HEAVY LIFTING.

23:37.709 --> 23:39.667
I'M GLAD I COULD HELP.
I WAS A FAN.

23:39.750 --> 23:40.875
[ LAUGHS ]

23:40.959 --> 23:41.709
HEY, DOC. USUAL?

23:41.792 --> 23:43.291
UH, YES.

23:43.375 --> 23:45.834
AND WHATEVER <i>SHE'S</i> HAVING.

23:45.917 --> 23:48.250
THANK YOU.

23:50.875 --> 23:54.333
Delaney:
OH, HEY, DYING VIRGIN BOY...

23:54.417 --> 23:56.208
YOU WANT TO PRICK ME?

23:56.291 --> 23:58.041
WHAT? YEAH.

23:58.125 --> 23:59.417
WAIT, WHAT?

23:59.500 --> 24:01.417
HERE. [ Singsong voice ]
LOOK WHAT I FOUND.

24:05.291 --> 24:07.375
COME HERE.

24:07.458 --> 24:08.667
HOLD THIS.

24:08.750 --> 24:10.083
ARE YOU SUPPOSED
TO HAVE THIS?

24:12.083 --> 24:14.083
OH.

24:18.125 --> 24:20.750
OKAY.

24:20.834 --> 24:23.458
ALL SET. DO ME.

24:23.542 --> 24:24.542
YOU WANT ME TO PIERCE
YOUR BELLYBUTTON?

24:24.625 --> 24:26.542
UH-HUH, ON THREE.

24:26.625 --> 24:28.041
1, 2...

24:28.125 --> 24:29.375
NO, WAIT.

24:29.458 --> 24:30.875
MM!

24:30.959 --> 24:33.625
OOH! 3.

24:33.709 --> 24:34.750
THIS IS INSANE.

24:34.834 --> 24:37.041
[ GRUNTS ]

24:37.125 --> 24:40.750
OOH!
THANKS FOR THE ASSIST.

24:44.333 --> 24:46.375
WAIT.

24:46.458 --> 24:47.709
ARE YOU REALLY A VIRGIN?

24:47.792 --> 24:50.000
[ SCOFFS ]

24:50.083 --> 24:51.792
COME ON, NOW, BABY DOLL.

24:51.875 --> 24:54.542
WHY WOULD I LIE ABOUT SOMETHING
SO EMBARRASSING?

24:54.625 --> 24:56.875
SO, IF WE HAVE SEX RIGHT NOW,

24:56.959 --> 24:59.875
THIS IS POTENTIALLY SOMETHING
YOU'RE GONNA REMEMBER

24:59.959 --> 25:01.041
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE?

25:01.125 --> 25:02.834
[ SCOFFS ]

25:02.917 --> 25:05.000
I'M ALREADY GONNA REMEMBER THIS
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE.

25:05.083 --> 25:07.625
GOOD ANSWER.

25:09.166 --> 25:10.667
MISSION ACCOMPLISHED.

25:10.750 --> 25:12.250
DUDE!

25:12.333 --> 25:14.417
SERIOUSLY?!

25:14.500 --> 25:16.250
[ PILLS RATTLE ]

25:16.333 --> 25:17.917
HELLO, FRIENDS.

25:18.000 --> 25:19.375
WAIT A MINUTE.

25:19.458 --> 25:21.000
I ONLY SEE EIGHT PILLS HERE.

25:21.083 --> 25:23.458
THAT'S ALL I COULD GET.
EIGHT PILLS, EIGHT MINUTES.

25:23.542 --> 25:25.375
ALL I NEED IS <i>FIVE</i> MINUTES.

25:25.458 --> 25:26.500
NOT A SELLING POINT.

25:26.583 --> 25:27.917
[ SIGHS ]

25:28.000 --> 25:29.792
YOU DID GOOD.

25:29.875 --> 25:31.166
COME SIT.

25:31.250 --> 25:32.291
[ DING! ]

25:32.375 --> 25:34.166
<i>THEY SAY THREE'S COMPANY.</i>

25:34.250 --> 25:37.250
<i>ACTUALLY, I HAVE NO IDEA</i>
<i>WHAT THAT MEANS.</i>

25:37.333 --> 25:38.959
PLAY ME SOMETHING.

25:39.041 --> 25:40.417
UM, I THOUGHT THE DEAL WAS

25:40.500 --> 25:42.583
I WOULD GET TO PLAY
FOR YOUR MANAGER.

25:42.667 --> 25:44.125
YEAH, YOU WILL.

25:44.208 --> 25:46.041
BUT YOU'VE GOT TO GET
THROUGH ME FIRST.

25:49.542 --> 25:51.542
YO, MAN, THIS BETTER BE THE
SHORTEST SONG IN THE WORLD.

25:54.125 --> 26:00.542
♪ OH, OH, OH, OH-OH ♪

26:00.625 --> 26:06.041
♪ OH, OH, OH, OH-OH ♪

26:06.125 --> 26:09.291
♪ THIS IS THE LIFE
WE LIVE ♪

26:09.375 --> 26:12.792
♪ YOU KNOW,
LIVING ON A SHOESTRING ♪

26:12.875 --> 26:15.125
♪ THIS IS THE FIGHT
WE'RE IN ♪

26:15.208 --> 26:18.917
♪ YOU KNOW,
DANCING IN A BULLRING ♪

26:19.000 --> 26:24.458
♪ IT'S ALL INSIDE A BREATH,
SO LET'S NOT GO WASTING IT ♪

26:24.542 --> 26:27.667
♪ 'CAUSE THERE'S JUST ONE LIFE
WE GET ♪

26:27.750 --> 26:30.667
♪ YOU KNOW,
YOU KNOW, KNOW, KNOW ♪

26:30.750 --> 26:35.000
♪ OH, OH, OH, OH-OH ♪

26:35.083 --> 26:36.834
♪ NOW IT'S FOREVER ♪

26:36.917 --> 26:39.583
♪ OH, OH, OH, OH-OH ♪
NO BOOK?

26:39.667 --> 26:43.000
NO BOOK.

26:43.083 --> 26:44.750
WHAT'S ALL THIS?

26:44.834 --> 26:46.834
WE HAVEN'T HAD THE BEST LUCK,
YOU AND ME, YOU KNOW?

26:46.917 --> 26:49.667
SUPPLY CLOSETS,
STRIP JOINTS,

26:49.750 --> 26:52.166
ONE TRULY TERRIBLE
HOMECOMING DANCE.

26:52.250 --> 26:54.458
SO, UH, I DECIDED TO START
AT THE VERY BEGINNING.

26:54.542 --> 26:55.667
I SEE.

26:55.750 --> 26:57.041
SO YOU'RE H.G. WELLS,

26:57.125 --> 26:58.667
AND THIS IS SOME SORT
OF TIME MACHINE?

26:58.750 --> 27:00.417
EXACTLY.

27:00.500 --> 27:02.417
AND TONIGHT, EMMA,
ON THIS ROOF,

27:02.500 --> 27:04.792
YOU AND I ARE GONNA HAVE THE
FIRST DATE WE SHOULD HAVE HAD,

27:04.875 --> 27:06.166
YOU KNOW,
IF WE MET OUT THERE.

27:06.250 --> 27:07.667
OH, REALLY?
REALLY.

27:07.750 --> 27:09.291
AND ON OUR FIRST DATE,

27:09.375 --> 27:12.041
BECAUSE I'M BOTH A BIG SPENDER
AND A GENTLEMAN,

27:12.125 --> 27:14.834
I WOULD HAVE TAKEN YOU TO THE
BEST RESTAURANT IN BAKERSFIELD.

27:14.917 --> 27:16.417
WHICH ISN'T SAYING MUCH,
I KNOW,

27:16.500 --> 27:18.583
BUT, UH,
YOU GET THE DRIFT --

27:18.667 --> 27:20.417
WHITE TABLECLOTHS,
SHRIMP COCKTAILS, ALL THAT.

27:20.500 --> 27:23.250
OR SHRIMP PAD THAI FROM THE
PLACE NEXT DOOR TO THE HOSPITAL?

27:23.333 --> 27:25.083
WELL, YOU KNOW,
I HAD TO IMPROVISE A BIT.

27:25.166 --> 27:26.792
I LIKE IT.

27:26.875 --> 27:28.542
IT'S LIKE WHEN THE PEANUTS TRIED
TO HAVE THANKSGIVING.

27:28.625 --> 27:30.875
WELL, THAT'S NOT EXACTLY
THE EFFECT I WAS GOING FOR,

27:30.959 --> 27:32.417
BUT I'LL TAKE IT.

27:32.500 --> 27:35.041
SO, JUST OUT OF CURIOSITY,
HOW DID WE MEET?

27:35.125 --> 27:36.250
OUT THERE, I MEAN.

27:36.333 --> 27:39.834
FORENSICS --
SPEECH AND DEBATE,

27:39.917 --> 27:41.709
NOT THE DEAD-BODY KIND.

27:41.792 --> 27:43.583
WE HAD THIS TOURNAMENT
AT THIS SNOTTY GIRLS' SCHOOL,

27:43.667 --> 27:46.208
WHERE YOU WERE A SCHOLARSHIP
STUDENT, OBVIOUSLY.

27:46.291 --> 27:47.917
UH, WHAT WAS THAT PLACE
CALLED AGAIN?

27:48.000 --> 27:49.458
MARLBOROUGH.

27:49.542 --> 27:51.083
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU DID
SPEECH AND DEBATE.

27:51.166 --> 27:53.792
WELL, SEE? THIS IS EXACTLY
WHAT FIRST DATES ARE FOR --

27:53.875 --> 27:56.583
LEARNING INCREDIBLY BORING
THINGS ABOUT EACH OTHER.

27:56.667 --> 27:59.291
[ CHUCKLES ]
AND WHAT HAPPENED --

27:59.375 --> 28:01.917
I GOT LOST...

28:02.000 --> 28:03.667
WHILE LOOKING
FOR THE BATHROOM.

28:03.750 --> 28:06.000
AND THERE YOU WERE,

28:06.083 --> 28:08.083
SITTING BY YOURSELF
IN THE LIBRARY.

28:08.166 --> 28:10.583
SO, DID YOU WIN
THE TOURNAMENT?

28:10.667 --> 28:15.250
NO. NO, BUT, UH...I MET YOU,
SO...

28:15.333 --> 28:17.500
I DON'T CARE.

28:24.083 --> 28:25.417
DO YOU SMELL SMOKE?

28:25.500 --> 28:28.959
OH, MY GOD, LEO, YOUR LEG!

28:30.792 --> 28:34.333
<i>I KNOW LOVE CAN SOMETIMES</i>
<i>BE DESCRIBED AS BURNING,</i>

28:34.417 --> 28:37.792
<i>BUT THERE'S NOTHING ROMANTIC</i>
<i>ABOUT THIS MOMENT.</i>

28:37.875 --> 28:41.875
HONESTLY, IF THAT IS WHAT
ONLINE DATING IS LIKE,

28:41.959 --> 28:43.959
I DON'T THINK I'M READY.

28:44.041 --> 28:46.458
NO. NO ONE EVER IS.

28:46.542 --> 28:47.959
THAT'S TRUE.
YEAH.

28:48.041 --> 28:49.667
BUT WHAT'S
THE ALTERNATIVE?

28:49.750 --> 28:51.917
JUST DYING ALONE.

28:52.000 --> 28:53.166
DARK.
WHOA!

28:53.250 --> 28:55.000
I'M SORRY.
THAT WAS DARK.

28:55.083 --> 28:57.000
YOU SHOULD NOT BE COMING TO <i>ME</i>
FOR ADVICE RIGHT NOW.

28:57.083 --> 28:58.583
ACCORDING TO
MY EX-GIRLFRIEND,

28:58.667 --> 29:03.041
I'M CHILDISH, I'M IMMATURE,
I'M SELFISH.

29:03.125 --> 29:04.542
SELFISH?
MM-HMM.

29:04.625 --> 29:08.458
NO. YOU ARE A DOCTOR
WHO HELPS SICK CHILDREN.

29:08.542 --> 29:11.458
UH, YOU'RE AMAZING.
MM.

29:11.542 --> 29:14.208
I'M SURE YOU'VE MADE
SOME MISTAKES.

29:14.291 --> 29:16.250
WE ALL DO.
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:16.333 --> 29:20.542
BUT YOU'RE A GOOD PERSON,
DR. McANDREW, I CAN TELL.

29:32.125 --> 29:35.166
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
BRITTANY.

29:35.250 --> 29:37.250
SORRY.
I'M SORRY, I'M SORRY.
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

29:37.333 --> 29:38.709
DO NOT APOLOGIZE, NO.

29:38.792 --> 29:41.333
[ BOTH CHUCKLE NERVOUSLY ]

29:41.417 --> 29:42.166
WE CAN'T.

29:42.250 --> 29:43.375
No!

29:43.458 --> 29:44.750
YEAH. OF COURSE.

29:44.834 --> 29:47.500
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.
YEAH.

29:53.750 --> 29:56.000
Hunter: WHERE YOU BEEN?

29:56.083 --> 30:00.583
I HAVE SEARCHED HIGH AND LOW,
BUT NO CONDOMS.

30:02.709 --> 30:04.375
NO PROBLEM.

30:04.458 --> 30:07.667
TURNS OUT S.T.I.s ARE ON THE
RISE IN THE GERIATRIC WARD.

30:07.750 --> 30:10.375
THEY HAVE A HUGE CONTAINER OF
THEM AT THE NURSES' STATION.

30:10.458 --> 30:12.166
THEY'RE BASICALLY
GIVING THEM AWAY

30:12.250 --> 30:14.041
LIKE MINTS
AT A CHINESE RESTAURANT.

30:17.542 --> 30:19.709
NOT EXACTLY THE REACTION
I EXPECTED.

30:19.792 --> 30:23.417
LOOK, I FEEL LIKE I HAVE TO
ADMIT SOMETHING TO YOU.

30:23.500 --> 30:24.834
I'VE SEEN THIS MOVIE.

30:24.917 --> 30:26.375
YOU'VE GOT SOME TERRIBLE
DISEASE, RIGHT?

30:26.458 --> 30:28.041
NO, WAIT. THAT'S ME.
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:28.125 --> 30:29.917
EITHER WAY,
WE'RE TOTALLY SCREWED HERE.

30:30.000 --> 30:31.750
YEAH, WE ARE.

30:31.834 --> 30:34.834
BUT THE TRUTH IS,
I'VE NEVER BEEN
IN A RELATIONSHIP

30:34.917 --> 30:37.208
THAT'S LASTED
MORE THAN THREE DAYS.

30:37.291 --> 30:39.750
AND THAT'S NOT BECAUSE I JUMP
INTO BED TOO QUICKLY.

30:39.834 --> 30:41.375
WAIT. WHO SAID THAT?

30:41.458 --> 30:44.875
IT'S, PERSONALLY, BECAUSE
I THINK I GET BORED.

30:47.375 --> 30:50.542
I GOT TO
ADMIT SOMETHING, TOO.

30:50.625 --> 30:53.250
I DON'T ACTUALLY KNOW
WHAT DAY WE'RE ON,

30:53.333 --> 30:55.417
HOW LONG
THIS IS GONNA LAST.

30:55.500 --> 30:57.083
ALL WE HAVE IS NOW,
THIS MOMENT.

30:57.166 --> 30:59.125
NOTHING ELSE IS GUARANTEED.

31:01.000 --> 31:03.959
YEAH, BUT ISN'T THAT TRUE
FOR EVERYONE?

31:07.166 --> 31:09.083
WHAT?
NOW YOU'RE, LIKE, MAD?

31:09.166 --> 31:10.375
NO. YOU'RE RIGHT.

31:10.458 --> 31:12.083
I NEVER THOUGHT ABOUT IT
THAT WAY.

31:12.166 --> 31:14.583
SO MAYBE WE SHOULD JUST BE
LIKE THE MINDLESS MASSES

31:14.667 --> 31:17.333
AND SEIZE SOME OTHER DAY,
LIKE...TOMORROW?

31:17.417 --> 31:19.375
TOMORROW.

31:19.458 --> 31:22.792
OF COURSE, I'VE NEVER WAITED
BEFORE, SO WHAT'S THAT LIKE?

31:22.875 --> 31:24.917
JUST A BUNCH OF LAME
HAND-HOLDING?

31:25.000 --> 31:26.792
[ CHUCKLES ]
PRETTY MUCH.

31:27.959 --> 31:29.291
OH, MY GOD.

31:29.375 --> 31:31.125
YOU'RE BURNING UP.
NO, NO.

31:31.208 --> 31:32.500
I'M JUST --
I'M JUST A LITTLE WARM.
ARE YOU SURE?

31:32.583 --> 31:36.000
[ GASPS ] HUNTER,
HUNTER, HUNTER!

31:36.083 --> 31:39.041
HELP, NURSE!
SOMEONE HELP!

31:40.542 --> 31:45.500
♪ SO DON'T BE AFRAID ♪

31:45.583 --> 31:48.333
♪ IT'S ALL GONNA BE OKAY ♪

31:48.417 --> 31:51.166
[ STRUMMING GUITAR ]

31:51.250 --> 31:54.709
♪ IT'S ALL GONNA BE OKAY ♪

32:04.000 --> 32:06.208
SO, WHAT'S THE VERDICT?

32:08.250 --> 32:10.208
YOU'RE GOOD.
YOU'RE <i>REALLY</i> GOOD.

32:10.291 --> 32:12.208
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:12.291 --> 32:15.709
BUT...I CAN'T INTRODUCE YOU
TO MY MANAGER.

32:15.792 --> 32:18.041
SERIOUSLY?

32:18.125 --> 32:19.291
WHY NOT?

32:19.375 --> 32:21.875
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY DATES

32:21.959 --> 32:25.000
I HAVE TO CANCEL
TO BE HERE?

32:25.083 --> 32:27.583
MY MANAGER'S LOSING PATIENCE
WITH ME.

32:27.667 --> 32:29.417
NEW BLOOD LIKE YOU COME IN,

32:29.500 --> 32:31.875
AND [Chuckling]
I'M OUT FOR SURE.

32:31.959 --> 32:32.959
YOU'RE A HUGE STAR.

32:33.041 --> 32:34.375
YOU'RE ACTUALLY AFRAID

32:34.458 --> 32:36.375
THAT THEY'RE GONNA LIKE ME
MORE THAN YOU?

32:36.458 --> 32:40.083
NO, I <i>KNOW</i> THEY'LL LIKE YOU
MORE THAN ME.

32:41.208 --> 32:43.583
YOU HAVE REAL TALENT.

32:43.667 --> 32:46.458
YOU SHOULD NEVER
DOUBT THAT.

32:46.542 --> 32:47.959
AND WHO KNOWS?

32:48.041 --> 32:50.375
YOU KNOW, MAYBE ONE DAY
I'LL SEE YOU AT THE VMAs

32:50.458 --> 32:51.417
OR SOMETHING --

32:51.500 --> 32:52.875
YOU KNOW, IF YOU --

32:52.959 --> 32:55.750
IF YOU DON'T, LIKE,
<i>DIE</i> OR SOMETHING.

32:55.834 --> 32:56.750
[ LAUGHS ]

32:56.834 --> 32:58.542
I'D SAY AT THIS POINT,

32:58.625 --> 33:01.625
MY CHANCES ARE ABOUT
AS GOOD AS YOURS.

33:01.709 --> 33:04.166
WAIT. HEY, HOLD ON.

33:05.542 --> 33:07.750
[ SIGHS ]

33:07.834 --> 33:09.333
HERE.

33:09.417 --> 33:12.000
FOR THE PILLS.

33:13.834 --> 33:15.083
THAT WASN'T OUR DEAL.

33:15.166 --> 33:16.834
I-I DON'T WANT YOUR MONEY.

33:16.917 --> 33:19.667
WELL...

33:19.750 --> 33:23.959
THE MONEY'S ALL I HAVE,
SO TAKE IT OR LEAVE IT.

33:33.875 --> 33:35.959
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

33:42.834 --> 33:44.458
THOSE ARE HIS PARENTS,
RIGHT?

33:44.542 --> 33:46.375
OH, GOD.
THIS MUST BE BAD.

33:46.458 --> 33:47.458
THEY WOULDN'T HAVE CALLED HIS
PARENTS IN IF THIS WASN'T BAD.

33:47.542 --> 33:48.750
CALM DOWN, KARA.

33:48.834 --> 33:50.083
HE'S GONNA BE OKAY,
THOUGH, RIGHT?

33:50.166 --> 33:51.458
JUST TELL ME
THAT HE'S GONNA BE OKAY.

33:51.542 --> 33:52.875
PEOPLE WITH LIVER FAILURE

33:52.959 --> 33:54.291
HAVE AN INCREASED RISK
OF INFECTION.

33:54.375 --> 33:57.208
THAT'S ALL I CAN TELL YOU.

33:57.291 --> 33:59.458
NOW, IT'S LATE.

33:59.542 --> 34:00.792
GO BACK TO YOUR ROOM
AND GO TO BED.

34:00.875 --> 34:02.208
YOU NEED YOUR REST, TOO.
WHAT? NO!

34:02.291 --> 34:04.083
I'M STAYING HERE
SO I CAN SEE EVERYTHING.

34:04.166 --> 34:06.166
I SAID IT'S LATE,
AND YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY UPSET.

34:06.250 --> 34:07.667
OH, IS THIS BAD
FOR MY HEART?

34:07.750 --> 34:08.875
NO.

34:08.959 --> 34:10.458
IN THIS CASE,

34:10.542 --> 34:12.250
IT'S A SIGN THAT IT'S
FUNCTIONING NORMALLY.

34:15.500 --> 34:17.667
DO YOU REMEMBER WHAT I TOLD YOU
THIS MORNING?

34:17.750 --> 34:19.083
THAT I SHOULDN'T HAVE SEX

34:19.166 --> 34:21.041
BECAUSE I'LL HAVE A HEART ATTACK
AND DIE.

34:21.125 --> 34:22.500
NO.

34:22.583 --> 34:24.834
I SAID YOU WERE
GOING TO GET HURT.

34:29.959 --> 34:33.000
MY JOB IS TO PROTECT
YOUR HEART, KARA,

34:33.083 --> 34:35.667
IN EVERY POSSIBLE WAY.

34:35.750 --> 34:37.917
♪ THEY COULD COME ALONG ♪

34:38.000 --> 34:42.166
♪ I WISH THEY'D BEEN TOLD ♪

34:42.250 --> 34:46.375
♪ THEY MAY CALL IT
A SHOT IN THE DARK ♪

34:46.458 --> 34:49.083
♪ FROM WHAT WE KNOW ♪

34:49.166 --> 34:53.041
♪ IT'S NOT UNHEARD OF ♪

34:53.125 --> 34:55.667
♪ AND WE'LL ONE DAY ♪

34:55.750 --> 34:57.041
[ SMOOCHING ]

34:57.125 --> 34:58.792
GOOD MORNING!

34:58.875 --> 35:00.750
♪ TELL OUR STORY ♪

35:00.834 --> 35:02.250
HEY.
HEY.

35:02.333 --> 35:04.375
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

35:04.458 --> 35:07.542
SO, UM, I-I, UH --

35:07.625 --> 35:12.125
HOW DO YOU WANT TO PLAY THIS,
YOU KNOW, AT -- AT WORK?

35:14.125 --> 35:16.375
UH, WELL...

35:16.458 --> 35:17.917
I-I DON'T KNOW.

35:18.000 --> 35:19.083
YOU KNOW, I WAS --

35:19.166 --> 35:21.041
I WAS HOPING THAT,
YOU KNOW,

35:21.125 --> 35:23.375
WE COULD KEEP THIS BETWEEN US,
I MEAN, THIS --

35:23.458 --> 35:28.792
[ LAUGHS ] WELL, I MEAN, SURE,
LIKE, YOU KNOW, AT FIRST.

35:28.875 --> 35:32.000
BUT, UH, PEOPLE ARE GONNA
FIGURE IT OUT.

35:32.083 --> 35:36.333
THEY'RE GONNA BE ABLE TO TELL
THAT WE'RE, YOU KNOW, TOGETHER.

35:39.583 --> 35:40.542
[ LAUGHS ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:40.625 --> 35:42.667
YEAH, UM...

35:44.834 --> 35:48.250
YEAH, I WAS, UH --

35:48.333 --> 35:50.250
I WAS HOPING
THAT MAYBE THIS IS,

35:50.333 --> 35:52.208
LIKE, MORE OF A, UH --

35:52.291 --> 35:55.250
LIKE A ONE-TIME THING,
YOU KNOW?

35:57.208 --> 35:58.917
HEY, YOU KNOW,
LIKE Y-Y-YOU GO OUT,

35:59.000 --> 36:00.417
AND YOU HAVE --
YOU HAVE FUN.

36:00.500 --> 36:01.583
YOU KNOW,
YOU LET SOME STEAM OFF.

36:01.667 --> 36:03.625
NO. I...

36:03.709 --> 36:06.667
I MEAN, NO, I <i>DON'T.</i>

36:08.583 --> 36:10.000
BUT YOU DID.
YOU...

36:12.375 --> 36:15.500
NO, UH, BRITTANY, I MEAN, UH,
THAT CAME OUT SO WRONG.

36:15.583 --> 36:17.625
I'M SO SORRY FOR SAYING IT
LIKE -- OKAY, YOU'RE MAD.

36:17.709 --> 36:19.417
UH, I UNDERSTAND
THAT YOU'RE MAD.

36:19.500 --> 36:21.458
IT DOESN'T HAVE TO BE
LIKE THIS, BRITTANY.

36:21.542 --> 36:23.208
THIS IS LIKE -- I MEAN,

36:23.291 --> 36:25.834
GEEZ, HAVEN'T YOU EVER HAD
A ONE-NIGHT STAND BEFORE?

36:25.917 --> 36:27.792
OW!

36:27.875 --> 36:30.417
<i>SO I GUESS THAT EXPLAINS</i>
<i>THE BLACK EYE.</i>

36:30.500 --> 36:32.000
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

36:32.083 --> 36:36.125
<i>AS FOR THE BLACKENED LEG...</i>

36:36.208 --> 36:38.417
I WANTED TO STOP BY
AND GIVE YOU THIS.

36:38.500 --> 36:40.625
IT'S THE ONLY THING
I MANAGED TO SAVE

36:40.709 --> 36:42.625
FROM LAST NIGHT'S
CONFLAGRATION.

36:42.709 --> 36:44.417
WHO NEEDS A PRESENT
WHEN YOU'VE GOT SOMEONE

36:44.500 --> 36:46.166
WHO KNOWS HOW TO USE THE WORD
"CONFLAGRATION"?

36:46.250 --> 36:48.834
I KNOW, AND IT'S MY WAY
OF SAYING I'M IN.

36:48.917 --> 36:51.333
AND WE'LL GET THROUGH THIS,
YOU KNOW, WHATEVER HAPPENS.

36:58.000 --> 36:59.625
CHOCOLATES?

36:59.709 --> 37:02.834
YOU DON'T LIKE CHOCOLATE?

37:02.917 --> 37:07.125
YOU DO UNDERSTAND
THAT I'M ANOREXIC, RIGHT?

37:07.208 --> 37:10.333
I MEAN, DO YOU -- DO YOU
GET THAT ON <i>ANY</i> LEVEL?

37:10.417 --> 37:12.166
GET WHAT?
I-I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

37:12.250 --> 37:14.667
I'M NOT GONNA EAT A BOX
OF FREAKING CHOCOLATE, LEO.

37:14.750 --> 37:16.125
I THOUGHT YOU WERE BETTER.

37:16.208 --> 37:18.333
THEY WOULDN'T BE SENDING
YOU HOME IF --

37:18.417 --> 37:21.166
I'M NOT BETTER, OKAY?
I'M NOT BETTER!

37:21.250 --> 37:23.667
AND I KEEP WAITING FOR
SOMEONE TO FIGURE THAT
OUT, AND THEY DON'T!

37:23.750 --> 37:25.333
I MEAN,
OF COURSE THEY DON'T,

37:25.417 --> 37:26.709
'CAUSE AS LONG AS I SAY
THE RIGHT THING

37:26.792 --> 37:28.291
AND I ACT THE RIGHT WAY,
THEY'RE HAPPY,

37:28.375 --> 37:30.333
BECAUSE THAT MEANS
THAT THEY CURED ME, RIGHT?

37:30.417 --> 37:32.542
IT'S JUST LIKE WHEN I EAT
IN FRONT OF YOU.

37:32.625 --> 37:35.041
YOU GET SO PROUD,
LIKE YOU'RE SOME TYPE OF HERO,

37:35.125 --> 37:36.750
LIKE YOU FIXED ME
OR SOMETHING!

37:36.834 --> 37:38.750
OH, MY GOD.
EMMA, I NEVER WANTED TO FIX YOU.

37:38.834 --> 37:40.542
I JUST WANTED --
YOU WANTED ME TO BE NORMAL.

37:40.625 --> 37:42.709
I KNOW. BUT I'M NOT,
AND I'M NEVER GONNA BE.

37:42.792 --> 37:44.917
DON'T SAY THAT, EMMA.
I KNOW YOU, AND THIS --

37:45.000 --> 37:46.709
NO, YOU DON'T!

37:46.792 --> 37:49.208
I KEEP THINKING THAT YOU DO,
LEO, BUT YOU DON'T!

37:52.959 --> 37:56.959
YOU NEVER HAVE,
AND YOU NEVER WILL.

38:02.959 --> 38:06.041
YOUR CANCER'S GONE, LEO.
CONGRATULATIONS.

38:06.125 --> 38:07.542
YOU'RE GOING HOME.

38:07.625 --> 38:10.542
AND WHEN YOU DO,
YOU CAN JUST FORGET ALL ABOUT ME

38:10.625 --> 38:12.625
AND PRETEND LIKE THIS
NEVER HAPPENED.

38:19.834 --> 38:21.959
LET ME JUST SAY THE ONLY REASON
WE'RE HERE IN THE FIRST PLACE

38:22.041 --> 38:23.667
IS 'CAUSE YOU'RE SUCH
A KILLER ATHLETE.

38:23.750 --> 38:25.333
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:25.417 --> 38:27.083
I DIDN'T SEE IT AT FIRST,
'CAUSE YOU WERE SLACKING OFF,

38:27.166 --> 38:29.500
MISSING APPOINTMENTS.
I KNOW, UH,

38:29.583 --> 38:31.333
I DIDN'T HAVE THE BEST ATTITUDE
AT FIRST.

38:31.417 --> 38:33.250
BUT I'VE BEEN PLAYING SPORTS
MY WHOLE LIFE,

38:33.333 --> 38:35.625
AND I KNOW THAT IF I APPLIED
THE SAME DISCIPLINE TO THIS,

38:35.709 --> 38:37.125
EVERYTHING WILL JUST
GET EASIER.

38:37.208 --> 38:39.417
THAT'S TRUE.
AND YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

38:39.500 --> 38:42.250
EVERYONE'S BEEN AMAZED BY
THE PROGRESS AND THE DEDICATION.

38:42.333 --> 38:44.083
BUT THE POWERS THAT BE
ARE THINKING

38:44.166 --> 38:47.875
AT LEAST ONE MORE WEEK,
POSSIBLY TWO.

38:47.959 --> 38:49.625
WHAT? [ SCOFFS ]

38:49.709 --> 38:50.750
I'M SORRY, LEO.

38:50.834 --> 38:53.417
I TRIED.

39:00.542 --> 39:03.625
<i>HERE'S ANOTHER CHOICE</i>
<i>THAT MIGHT NOT BE THE BEST --</i>

39:03.709 --> 39:06.792
<i>TAKING DRUG MONEY</i>
<i>FROM A POP STAR.</i>

39:06.875 --> 39:09.667
<i>BUT IT HELPED JORDI</i>
<i>GET WHERE HE'S GOING.</i>

39:09.750 --> 39:10.917
<i>I'M NOT JUDGING.</i>

39:11.000 --> 39:13.625
♪ ...WHAT YOU THOUGHT ♪

39:13.709 --> 39:15.125
♪ YEAH ♪

39:15.208 --> 39:17.291
OH, MY GOD, WHAT HAPPENED?

39:17.375 --> 39:21.458
UH, IT WAS A, UH,
BAR FIGHT.

39:21.542 --> 39:23.917
THAT DOESN'T SOUND
LIKE YOU.

39:24.000 --> 39:25.625
DOESN'T IT?

39:25.709 --> 39:28.041
IMMATURE, IRRESPONSIBLE,
SOPHOMORIC.

39:28.125 --> 39:30.125
I MEAN,
THESE ARE JUST A-A FEW

39:30.208 --> 39:32.709
OF THE GEMS THAT
YOU DROPPED YESTERDAY.

39:32.792 --> 39:36.375
MM,
I NEVER SAID "SOPHOMORIC."

39:38.458 --> 39:41.959
COME ON.
SIT DOWN, SIT DOWN.
ALL RIGHT. [ SIGHS ]

39:52.959 --> 39:54.709
I'M SORRY.

39:57.125 --> 39:58.917
I'M SORRY FOR YESTERDAY.

39:59.000 --> 40:00.834
I'M SORRY FOR EVERYTHING.

40:00.917 --> 40:03.625
IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHO BROKE UP WITH WHO.

40:03.709 --> 40:06.083
THE POINT IS, IS THAT YOU WERE
RIGHT TO MOVE ON, AND --

40:06.166 --> 40:07.250
<i>YOU</i> WERE RIGHT.

40:07.333 --> 40:08.667
WHAT?

40:08.750 --> 40:11.834
I STILL THINK ABOUT YOU.

40:11.917 --> 40:16.000
BACK IN AFRICA,
I WAS CERTAIN ABOUT SAM,

40:16.083 --> 40:17.500
AND NOW I DON'T KNOW.

40:17.583 --> 40:19.500
AND I'M NOT GONNA SAY
ANYTHING ELSE,

40:19.583 --> 40:21.375
BECAUSE THAT'S ALL
I'M SURE OF.

40:21.458 --> 40:23.917
I'M JUST VERY...

40:24.000 --> 40:25.542
CONFUSED. [ SIGHS ]

40:56.625 --> 41:00.500
HEY. WHAT'S GOING ON?
YOU SWITCHING ROOMS?

41:01.625 --> 41:03.875
LOOK,
I KNOW YOU'RE MAD AT ME.

41:03.959 --> 41:05.750
I JUST CAME TO SAY THAT...

41:05.834 --> 41:07.625
YOU WERE WRONG.

41:07.709 --> 41:09.417
I'M NOT GETTING OUT.

41:09.500 --> 41:11.583
APPARENTLY,
I NEED MORE TIME.

41:11.667 --> 41:13.083
BUT IT'S GOOD.
IT MEANS WE CAN WORK THIS OUT,

41:13.166 --> 41:14.500
YOU KNOW, AND STILL BE
IN HERE TOGETHER.

41:14.583 --> 41:16.917
ACTUALLY, NO.

41:17.000 --> 41:18.458
I HAD MY MEETING
WITH DR. SAMUELS,

41:18.542 --> 41:20.083
AND SHE SAID
THAT I COULD GO.

41:20.166 --> 41:23.417
MY DAD'S HERE NOW.
HE'S FILLING OUT PAPERWORK.

41:23.500 --> 41:24.917
THEY RELEASED YOU?

41:25.000 --> 41:26.583
THEY DID.

41:26.667 --> 41:28.917
EMMA, YOU CAN'T GO.
YOU'RE STILL SICK.

41:29.000 --> 41:30.166
YOU CAN'T JUST LEAVE!

41:30.250 --> 41:31.291
[ ZIPPER CLICKS ]

41:31.375 --> 41:33.041
BUT I AM.

41:33.125 --> 41:35.166
[ SIGHS ]
WELL, THAT'S DONE.

41:35.250 --> 41:37.792
UH, YOU...
ALL PACKED UP?

41:37.875 --> 41:39.583
YES.

41:39.667 --> 41:41.250
DAD, THIS IS LEO.

41:41.333 --> 41:42.917
PLEASED TO MEET YOU.

41:43.041 --> 41:44.667
LEO, IS IT?

41:44.750 --> 41:47.041
♪ WHAT IF I SAID I WOULD BREAK
YOUR HEART? ♪

41:47.125 --> 41:51.041
SO, UM, UH,
I'LL GET THIS ONE, SWEETIE.

41:51.125 --> 41:57.208
♪ WHAT IF I SAID I HAD PROBLEMS
THAT MADE ME MEAN? ♪

41:58.709 --> 42:00.041
I SEE YOU!

42:00.125 --> 42:02.834
EMMA, I KNOW YOU.

42:02.917 --> 42:04.875
I-I KNOW YOU'RE STRONG ENOUGH
TO DO THIS.

42:04.959 --> 42:07.583
YOU JUST GOT TO -- YOU GOT
TO TELL SOMEBODY THE TRUTH.

42:07.667 --> 42:09.625
PLEASE.

42:09.709 --> 42:13.250
♪ MAYBE YOU CAN STOP
BEFORE THIS STARTS ♪

42:13.333 --> 42:14.458
YOU COMING, SWEETIE?

42:14.542 --> 42:15.917
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

42:16.000 --> 42:17.834
ALL RIGHT.

42:17.917 --> 42:24.375
♪ MAYBE YOU CAN SEE THAT I JUST
MAY BE TOO CRAZY TO LOVE ♪

42:24.458 --> 42:29.500
♪ IF I TOLD YOU SOLITUDE
FITS ME LIKE A GLOVE ♪

42:29.583 --> 42:34.333
♪ WOULD YOU LET ME OUT? ♪

42:34.417 --> 42:36.291
IT WAS NICE TO MEET YOU.

42:36.375 --> 42:42.667
♪ YOU WANT TO KNOW
WHERE I'M COMING FROM ♪

42:42.750 --> 42:48.792
♪ I WAS ALONE
WHEN I BURNED MY HOME ♪

42:48.875 --> 42:56.458
♪ AND ALL OF THE PIECES
WERE TORN AND THROWN ♪

42:56.542 --> 43:01.083
♪ YOU SHOULD KNOW
WHERE I'M COMING FROM ♪

43:15.208 --> 43:18.125
